Description: Provides functions to read, clean, and reshape NONMEM listing
    (.lst) files into tidy data frames for downstream population
    pharmacokinetic and pharmacodynamic (PK/PD) analyses. Parsers extract
    THETA, OMEGA, SIGMA, objective function value (OFV), condition number,
    and shrinkage values from NONMEM output files. Both runs with and without
    a covariance step are handled gracefully, returning NA for unavailable
    quantities rather than raising errors.
